WEBVTT

01:38.940 --> 01:40.351
How is everything,
Mr. Sabian?

01:40.420 --> 01:41.865
Great, as always.
Good.

01:41.940 --> 01:44.022
You get home now, Eva.
It's getting late.

01:44.540 --> 01:46.190
Stay safe.

01:46.260 --> 01:48.661
Yeah. You, too,
Mr. Sabian.

01:48.740 --> 01:50.504
<i>Traffic is
building rapidly downtown,</i>

01:50.580 --> 01:53.424
<i>as citizens rush to get home
before commencement.</i>

01:53.500 --> 01:55.389
<i>If you're not Purging,
we advise you</i>

01:55.460 --> 01:57.260
<i>to get off the streets
as quickly as possible.</i>

01:57.300 --> 01:59.029
<i>It'll soon be
a war out there.</i>

01:59.260 --> 02:01.308
<i>Prognosticators estimate
that more people</i>

02:01.380 --> 02:02.461
<i>will partake in
this year's Purge...</i>

02:02.620 --> 02:04.384
Sabian's gone.
That's it.

02:04.540 --> 02:06.668
What is she waiting for? Why
doesn't this bitch let us go?

02:06.820 --> 02:09.265
Hey, calm down.
We got plenty of time.

02:09.340 --> 02:11.183
You girls up to
anything fun tonight?

02:11.300 --> 02:13.302
I might kidnap Eva
this year.

02:13.500 --> 02:15.070
Hope that's okay
with you, mami.

02:16.980 --> 02:18.345
It's getting late.

02:18.500 --> 02:20.980
Hope to see you all tomorrow.
Stay safe.

02:21.140 --> 02:22.266
Okay, stay safe.

02:22.340 --> 02:25.423
Finally.
Stay safe, Mrs. Crawley.

02:30.820 --> 02:32.709
Eva.

02:32.780 --> 02:34.270
Need a ride home?

02:34.420 --> 02:35.945
I'm fine, Carlos.

02:36.100 --> 02:40.264
Stay safe.

02:40.340 --> 02:42.502
Bye, Carlito.
Stay safe.

02:44.140 --> 02:46.950
If he asked to take me home,
I'd accept that ride, girl.

02:47.020 --> 02:48.146
He's a dog.

02:48.500 --> 02:51.344
Oh, I like that dog. I would
walk the shit out of that dog.

02:51.540 --> 02:53.460
But that dog doesn't want
anything to do with me,

02:53.500 --> 02:54.786
he wants to sniff
your ass.

02:54.860 --> 02:55.980
You're disgusting.

02:56.020 --> 02:57.385
It's true.

02:59.100 --> 03:01.023
You're really gonna
ask her tonight?

03:01.340 --> 03:02.785
I have to.

03:02.940 --> 03:05.386
I can't afford his
medicine much longer.

03:06.820 --> 03:08.868
All right, good luck.

03:10.100 --> 03:11.226
Stay safe.

03:12.500 --> 03:14.070
Stay safe, sweetie.

03:18.500 --> 03:19.911
Okay.

04:10.140 --> 04:12.820
<i>Both the people and
the government wanted the Purge.</i>

04:12.860 --> 04:14.703
<i>The New Founding
Fathers came into office...</i>

04:14.780 --> 04:17.101
<i>Were voted into office
by a country who wanted change...</i>

04:17.180 --> 04:19.945
<i>This new regime took
advantage of the nation's fear.</i>

04:28.700 --> 04:30.862
I'm glad we took
the back roads.

04:30.940 --> 04:33.910
The highways are probably
a mess right now.

04:34.380 --> 04:37.065
Yeah.
We'll be there in no time.

04:37.220 --> 04:38.426
Yeah.

04:48.220 --> 04:49.346
What are you looking at?

04:51.420 --> 04:54.310
Nothing.
Just, you know, stuff.

04:59.460 --> 05:00.746
Are you okay?

05:01.980 --> 05:04.586
Yeah. I'm fine.

05:06.300 --> 05:07.870
You sure?

05:08.300 --> 05:10.348
You don't need
to keep asking me.

05:17.660 --> 05:19.742
<i>My name is Donald Talbot.</i>

05:19.820 --> 05:23.108
<i>Our regime was voted into
office nine years ago.</i>

05:23.180 --> 05:24.909
<i>And the first
order of business</i>

05:24.980 --> 05:27.062
<i>was to deal with
the epidemic of crime</i>

05:27.140 --> 05:28.983
<i>that was plaguing
this nation.</i>

05:29.220 --> 05:32.110
<i>The answer was the Purge.</i>

05:37.140 --> 05:38.869
You need some protection tonight?
You need something?

05:38.940 --> 05:40.226
Hey, man,
we running out of...

05:40.300 --> 05:41.950
Hey, that Purge tonight,
y'all know what time it is.

05:42.020 --> 05:43.670
Hitting them in the face
ain't gonna work no more.

05:43.740 --> 05:45.151
You need
something powerful.

05:46.020 --> 05:47.101
How you doing, buddy?

05:47.180 --> 05:49.786
Use your hands, man. Just use your hands.
Don't even worry about it.

05:49.860 --> 05:51.430
Hey, sweetheart, how you doing?
How you doing?

05:51.500 --> 05:52.581
You gonna need something
for protection tonight?

05:52.700 --> 05:54.145
No. No, I'm good. I'm good.
UZI? Beretta?

05:54.220 --> 05:55.790
Look, on the cheap-cheap.

05:55.900 --> 05:58.301
Or a blade to cut your man's throat?
Whatever you need.

05:58.780 --> 06:00.862
We take any kind
of payment.

06:09.540 --> 06:10.541
Eva!

06:10.660 --> 06:12.583
Hey, Diego. What's up, girl?
How you doing?

06:12.700 --> 06:14.350
Good. How you doing?
Yeah? Everything's great?

06:14.500 --> 06:15.740
No, it's not great.
I'm tired...

06:15.820 --> 06:16.946
Oh, it could be better.

06:17.020 --> 06:18.749
Take me up there with you tonight.
Get a little protection.

06:18.820 --> 06:19.820
You know what I'm saying?

06:19.900 --> 06:20.981
Come on, now. I'm cool, Diego.
I'm good.

06:21.060 --> 06:22.061
You sure you don't
want no protection?

06:22.140 --> 06:23.141
Huh?
No, thanks, Diego.

06:23.220 --> 06:25.020
I'm the man for the job.
You know what I mean?

06:25.060 --> 06:28.746
<i>We've lost our
souls to attain this peace.</i>

06:29.580 --> 06:32.424
<i>We no longer worship
at the altar of Christ,</i>

06:32.700 --> 06:35.590
<i>Muhammad, Yahweh.</i>

06:35.740 --> 06:39.347
<i>We worship at the altar
of Smith & Wesson.</i>

06:39.420 --> 06:42.424
<i>We, the people,
know not what we do.</i>

06:42.580 --> 06:45.789
Horseshit. Where'd
you find this lunatic?

06:45.900 --> 06:47.664
I saw his protest posters
all around the neighborhood.

06:47.860 --> 06:49.430
He lives here, Papa.
He's just like us.

06:49.500 --> 06:52.868
Now, shush. Please listen. He's
not a lunatic.

06:52.940 --> 06:55.341
<i>The Purge is not about
containing crime to one night,</i>

06:55.420 --> 06:58.424
<i>and cleansing our souls
by releasing aggression.</i>

06:58.500 --> 07:01.629
<i>It's about one thing.
Money.</i>

07:02.420 --> 07:06.061
<i>Who dies tonight? The poor.</i>

07:06.580 --> 07:09.265
<i>We can't afford to
protect ourselves.</i>

07:09.460 --> 07:11.189
That's enough.
I can't listen to this crap.

07:11.300 --> 07:12.580
He's as full of shit
as they are.

07:12.620 --> 07:15.305
No, he's right. Come on. They're
keeping the population down

07:15.380 --> 07:17.621
by getting rid of people
like us to save money.

07:17.780 --> 07:19.862
Talk is cheap, Cali.
Mmm-hmm.

07:19.940 --> 07:22.420
He may be right, but he
won't do anything about it.

07:22.860 --> 07:24.544
Home.

07:29.780 --> 07:30.827
Hey, Daddy.

07:30.940 --> 07:33.466
Don't "hey, Daddy" me.
Where have you been?

07:33.540 --> 07:35.349
We're less than two hours
until commencement,

07:35.460 --> 07:36.746
and you're out gallivanting.

07:36.820 --> 07:38.310
Gallivanting? I was
picking up your medicine.

07:38.460 --> 07:41.464
Even worse.
A waste of time and money.

07:41.660 --> 07:43.788
Christ, Eva, I told you
not to get this stuff.

07:43.860 --> 07:45.464
I'm tired of listening
to this every day.

07:45.540 --> 07:46.871
It does nothing...
I'm not taking it!

07:46.980 --> 07:48.823
You're taking your medicine. I'm
not taking it! No, I'm not!

07:48.900 --> 07:51.141
Yes, you are! I'm not taking it.
You're taking it back.

07:51.220 --> 07:52.790
Oh, my God, really?

07:52.860 --> 07:53.861
Can we stop?

07:56.780 --> 08:00.182
Look, Papa, maybe it doesn't do
anything, but can you just take it?

08:00.620 --> 08:02.190
For me?

08:06.820 --> 08:08.185
Okay-

08:08.340 --> 08:11.742
We'll lockdown and then
we'll eat after commencement.

08:11.860 --> 08:12.986
Count me out.

08:13.860 --> 08:16.784
I'm gonna take a long nap,
and don't bother me.

08:17.260 --> 08:20.343
I'm gonna try to sleep through
this godforsaken holiday.

08:24.140 --> 08:27.861
Look, I'm sorry
I'm so grumpy, girls.

08:28.460 --> 08:30.667
I hate this night.

08:31.100 --> 08:33.865
Please, forgive me.

08:39.220 --> 08:41.587
You drive me crazy.

08:45.900 --> 08:47.106
Uh...

08:47.540 --> 08:49.781
Make sure you
lockdown everything.

08:51.180 --> 08:53.387
I'll take care of my room.

08:55.140 --> 08:56.824
I love you both.

08:57.540 --> 08:59.224
Very much.

09:01.220 --> 09:02.745
I know.

09:10.340 --> 09:12.229
That was weird.

09:12.420 --> 09:14.070
It must be the night.

09:15.180 --> 09:16.341
Yeah.

09:17.740 --> 09:20.220
I'm gonna take a quick shower,
and then we'll lockdown.

09:20.380 --> 09:23.190
Okay, wait. How did things go with Mrs.
Crawley?

09:23.700 --> 09:25.589
Did you get the raise?

09:28.060 --> 09:30.108
God, what a bitch.

09:30.260 --> 09:31.591
Well, did you at least
make a good argument?

09:31.660 --> 09:34.186
Did you say everything
that we practiced?

09:36.780 --> 09:38.430
I'm sorry, baby.

09:40.260 --> 09:41.705
Yeah.

09:57.460 --> 09:59.349
I want to tell her, Shane.

10:07.140 --> 10:09.461
Hey, did you hear me?

10:09.780 --> 10:11.191
I said I wanna tell
your sister...

10:11.260 --> 10:12.625
Yeah, I heard you.

10:12.700 --> 10:15.749
I just don't feel
like telling her.

10:16.380 --> 10:17.620
Why?

10:19.460 --> 10:22.384
Because as soon as you say it
out loud to another person,

10:23.220 --> 10:25.063
then it's irreversible.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.062
Do you have the keys?

10:29.220 --> 10:30.426
Yeah.

10:30.660 --> 10:31.946
Handy?

10:32.300 --> 10:33.426
Right here.

10:34.300 --> 10:35.586
Can you unlock
the car, please?

10:35.660 --> 10:36.821
It's unlocked.

10:37.220 --> 10:38.460
No, it's not.

10:38.820 --> 10:39.981
There.

11:31.340 --> 11:32.865
Let's just get
in the car.

11:37.220 --> 11:38.585
What the fuck
was that all about?

11:38.740 --> 11:40.868
I don't know.
He didn't tell me.

11:40.940 --> 11:43.307
You know, we don't have a whole lot
of time before commencement, Shane.

11:43.380 --> 11:46.509
All right.
We'll be fine, I promise.

12:02.900 --> 12:03.901
Yeah.

12:06.900 --> 12:08.743
I've been calling.
Why didn't you pick up?

12:10.260 --> 12:11.750
What do you want?

12:20.620 --> 12:22.668
You can't go out there. You
know how dangerous it is...

12:22.740 --> 12:24.265
You need to go.
You need to leave.

12:26.540 --> 12:28.110
It's late.

12:29.660 --> 12:31.503
Don't do this.

12:33.260 --> 12:36.025
It won't make you
feel any better.

12:38.340 --> 12:40.263
Go with your new husband,

12:40.940 --> 12:43.227
and your new family.

12:44.660 --> 12:46.264
Leave.

12:53.660 --> 12:55.424
Just stay safe.

13:06.620 --> 13:08.224
You, too.

13:22.140 --> 13:24.507
<i>Whatever happened
to "Give me your needy,</i>

13:25.700 --> 13:27.907
<i>"your tired,</i>

13:27.980 --> 13:32.269
<i>"your huddled masses
yearning to breathe free"?</i>

13:32.980 --> 13:35.711
<i>The redistribution
of wealth upward</i>

13:35.780 --> 13:37.669
<i>through killing
has to stop.</i>

13:38.780 --> 13:40.589
<i>We must pick up arms.</i>

13:42.820 --> 13:45.664
<i>This year,
we will fight back!</i>

14:37.380 --> 14:39.587
Jeez, that guy
freaked me out.

14:39.900 --> 14:41.902
Did not
see him coming.

14:42.060 --> 14:44.870
I thought we decided
it was irreversible.

14:47.340 --> 14:49.946
No, you often decide
things on your own,

14:50.020 --> 14:52.148
and then pretend that they
were a joint decision.

14:52.260 --> 14:53.625
You often agree with me,

14:53.700 --> 14:54.826
and then
a week later say,

14:54.900 --> 14:56.420
"I don't remember
doing that."

14:56.500 --> 14:57.740
So, you're calling
me a liar?

14:57.900 --> 14:59.823
And you're calling
me a bully.

15:00.380 --> 15:02.064
Just say you changed
your mind,

15:02.140 --> 15:04.586
not that we didn't come
to a joint decision.

15:05.420 --> 15:07.104
This is the exact...

15:14.780 --> 15:17.863
See, this is exactly why we
need to tell your sister

15:17.940 --> 15:19.351
that we're separating.

15:19.860 --> 15:21.862
You're right,
it'll make it real,

15:21.940 --> 15:24.102
but I think we need
to make it real.

15:24.260 --> 15:26.501
Maybe I don't wanna
make it real.

15:30.580 --> 15:32.180
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

15:32.460 --> 15:33.621
What the hell is that?

15:33.700 --> 15:34.861
The power steering's gone.

15:34.940 --> 15:36.385
What do you mean
"the power steering's gone"?

15:36.460 --> 15:38.269
I don't know. There's
something wrong with the car.

15:38.420 --> 15:40.422
Can you pull over?
I'm trying.

15:50.860 --> 15:51.986
Shit.

15:52.060 --> 15:53.505
Try it again.

15:58.380 --> 16:00.030
It's dead.

16:23.300 --> 16:27.066
<i>The sixth Annual
Purge will begin in 45 minutes.</i>

16:45.820 --> 16:46.901
Just in case.

16:47.060 --> 16:48.107
Yeah.

16:51.460 --> 16:52.541
Hey-

16:53.420 --> 16:55.149
We're gonna be fine.

16:55.740 --> 16:57.504
Just like every year.

16:58.780 --> 17:00.191
Yeah.

17:02.060 --> 17:04.061
I'll pay three times as much
if you just come out here...

17:04.220 --> 17:06.507
No, no, no. I don't care about the car.
We just need a ride.

17:06.579 --> 17:07.780
It's... Hello?
Whoa, whoa! Hey!

17:08.780 --> 17:10.669
Hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa!

17:13.380 --> 17:15.064
Stop!
Shit.

17:15.220 --> 17:16.585
Please!

17:19.060 --> 17:21.540
Shane, we can't be stuck outside.
I know. I know.

17:21.740 --> 17:24.141
We're downtown. Everyone
comes downtown to Purge.

17:24.300 --> 17:25.869
Hey, hey.
Don't worry.

17:26.020 --> 17:28.500
We'll figure something
out, I promise.

17:31.100 --> 17:33.182
Is that coming
from our car?

17:37.620 --> 17:39.224
Oh, shit.

18:12.260 --> 18:14.388
He cut
those wires, Shane.

18:14.460 --> 18:15.507
Yeah.

18:22.340 --> 18:23.751
We need to run.

18:23.820 --> 18:24.821
Yeah, go, go.

18:35.340 --> 18:37.104
<i>News 13 wishes anyone</i>

18:37.180 --> 18:40.502
<i>who is not participating in this
year's Purge a safe evening</i>

18:40.580 --> 18:44.062
<i>and for those releasing the
beast, a successful cleanse.</i>

18:44.140 --> 18:45.187
<i>Good luck.</i>

18:45.260 --> 18:46.705
Should I get Papa?

18:47.180 --> 18:49.103
He hates this.
Let him sleep.

18:49.260 --> 18:50.750
<i>This is not a test.</i>

18:50.980 --> 18:53.381
<i>This is your Emergency
Broadcast System</i>

18:53.500 --> 18:55.707
<i>announcing the commencement
of The Annual Purge</i>

18:55.780 --> 18:58.181
<i>sanctioned by
the US Government.</i>

18:59.020 --> 19:00.909
<i>Weapons of Class 4 and lower</i>

19:00.980 --> 19:03.711
<i>have been authorized
for use during the Purge.</i>

19:03.860 --> 19:05.862
<i>All other weapons
are restricted.</i>

19:06.020 --> 19:09.502
<i>Government officials of ranking
10 have been granted immunity...</i>

19:13.260 --> 19:17.390
<i>Commencing at the siren, any and
all crime, including murder,</i>

19:17.540 --> 19:20.384
<i>will be legal
for 12 continuous hours.</i>

19:20.460 --> 19:23.748
<i>Police, fire and
emergency medical services</i>

19:23.820 --> 19:26.949
<i>will be unavailable until
tomorrow morning at 7:00 a.m.</i>

19:27.020 --> 19:28.545
<i>when the Purge concludes.</i>

19:28.740 --> 19:32.984
<i>Blessed be our New Founding Fathers,
and America, a nation reborn.</i>

19:33.100 --> 19:35.751
<i>May God be with you all. Let's go this way.
Let's just go.</i>

22:22.100 --> 22:24.307
Come on. Come on. Come on. Do you
think they're still after us?

22:24.420 --> 22:25.910
I have no idea.
Okay.

22:26.020 --> 22:27.909
Let's just get out of here.

22:30.580 --> 22:32.469
Oh, God! Let's get out of here.
Go!

22:35.340 --> 22:36.387
Where do we go?

22:36.900 --> 22:38.390
Here, get in this.
Get in this!

22:38.540 --> 22:40.907
We'll just hide in here.
Come on.

22:43.300 --> 22:44.540
- Go.
- Oh, God!

22:47.900 --> 22:49.186
Let's just get
out of here.

22:51.300 --> 22:52.711
Come on, come on.
You're good.

23:05.700 --> 23:07.111
Fuck, it's them.

23:07.820 --> 23:10.221
We gotta move, we gotta move.
We gotta move.

23:33.940 --> 23:35.863
I'm gonna go get
Papa for dinner.

23:36.020 --> 23:37.351
He said don't bother him.

23:37.500 --> 23:39.787
Yeah. I just wanna see
if he's awake.

23:45.620 --> 23:46.860
Mom!

23:47.780 --> 23:49.669
What? What is it?
Mom, come here!

23:50.780 --> 23:51.827
What's wrong?

23:52.380 --> 23:53.381
Where's Papa?

23:53.540 --> 23:54.780
Look at this.

23:56.780 --> 23:59.147
<i>"Dearest Eva and Cali,</i>

23:59.300 --> 24:02.463
<i>"my greatest heartache is seeing
the two girls I love so much</i>

24:02.540 --> 24:04.508
<i>"struggling in this world.</i>

24:05.260 --> 24:08.343
<i>"I am dying, you know this.</i>

24:09.540 --> 24:13.181
<i>"I'll be a martyr for
a wealthy family tonight.</i>

24:13.500 --> 24:15.821
<i>"They paid me
for this service.</i>

24:16.380 --> 24:20.749
<i>"$100,000 will be transferred
into your accounts, my darlings.</i>

24:22.180 --> 24:24.182
<i>"Take their money.</i>

24:24.340 --> 24:28.106
<i>"Survive the night and live a safe life.</i>

24:28.780 --> 24:30.191
<i>"I love you."</i>

24:32.260 --> 24:36.788
Blessed be America,
a nation reborn.

24:55.100 --> 24:57.023
I don't understand.

24:57.580 --> 25:00.424
It's how the wealthy Purge, baby.

25:01.380 --> 25:04.031
They buy poor
and sick people,

25:04.100 --> 25:05.829
and they take them
in their homes

25:05.900 --> 25:08.551
and they kill them
where they're safe.

25:09.300 --> 25:10.870
Oh, my God.

25:11.460 --> 25:13.906
It's just
like Carmelo said.

25:14.820 --> 25:17.340
Why would Papa do that? I don't
understand why he would do that.

25:18.940 --> 25:20.101
Okay, he must have
left something

25:20.220 --> 25:21.381
that could tell us
where he went.

25:21.460 --> 25:23.580
Cali. Cali. Like his phone.
We should call his phone.

25:23.660 --> 25:24.900
We could stop him.

25:25.100 --> 25:26.540
- Cali...
- Okay, that's fine.

25:26.580 --> 25:28.230
We can do something about this.
I don't know what,

25:28.340 --> 25:29.671
but we can still do something about it.
Cali, stop.

25:29.740 --> 25:31.071
Just stop. He's gone.

25:32.100 --> 25:33.545
He's gone.

26:14.940 --> 26:16.908
What is this?

26:18.580 --> 26:20.025
Who are they?
It looks like an army.

26:20.180 --> 26:22.262
I have no idea.

26:25.100 --> 26:26.704
It's them.
No, it can't be them.

26:26.860 --> 26:27.941
They haven't even
come inside yet.

26:28.020 --> 26:30.182
That was right in the other room.

26:36.740 --> 26:37.946
Eva!

26:38.900 --> 26:40.709
I'm here to protect you.

26:41.460 --> 26:43.588
